<subSubSection id="38477A42B5D082FC08F9AE8323E07C97" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="FC3ACFE5D89C890C8327E485675FC819" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName id="49B64FF9DA77E43329A1B845CA417DC0" authority="Jago, 1983 b" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Platyverticula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platyverticula ritchiei" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ritchiei">Platyverticula ritchiei Jago, 1983b</taxonomicName>
Fig. 59, 59A
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3F89B424D72246EE77D2DF260A29766F" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="3955F13B06DEA1432F1BF94461E2C44A" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="22C3D8385707806543C389373C47E3ED" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">-Holotype male and allotype female: SOMALIA, Kismayu, littoral dune slack in and around grounds of Wamu Hotel, 28.vii.1981, J.M. Ritchie (NHMUK).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0EA5B9A079D698D19CF6496261C40A5E" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph id="C3DC4B1972C2C8CE6C99C2CEAAD84C0A" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF6DB14790423A488E8CF14D7FA68278" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
-As for the genus. Figured in 
<bibRefCitation id="AC310B67A069ED9C7BFC6BC998D74578" author="Jago, ND" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the American Entomological Society" pageId="50" pageNumber="87" pagination="77 - 126" title="Flightless members of the Phlaeoba genus group in eastern and north-eastern Africa and their evolutionary convergence with the genus Odontomelus and its allies (Orthoptera, Acridoidea, Acrididae, Acridinae)." volume="109" year="1983 b">Jago (1983b)</bibRefCitation>
: 118, figs 52-56. Distinctive species with unique pronotal disc and genital structures in both sexes. Coloration in shades of dark and lighter browns, without any traces of brighter pigmentation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9D13559DBD51D259FFD185CDFED0BCB6" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="96E5B6F54E5BD2FA192D1F3A84414ECC" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B6C490111B457888B8F6173D38FE72C8" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
-Known only from the type locality in SOMALIA. According to the collector (cited in Jago l983b), the species occurs under 
<taxonomicName id="8219DF9A8E150B3B4785976D9236291E" class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Cordia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cordia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Cordia</taxonomicName>
sp. bushes, which are approximately 1 m high x 2 m in diameter, growing within 500 m of the high tide line; this zone integrates with trees and bushes some 18 m high, forming a woodland. The bushes on the dunes are separated by bare sand.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
